  <section id="fs-idp16181248" class="problems">
  <title>Problems</title>
  <exercise id="fs-idp123037088">
  <problem id="fs-idp5028032">
  <para id="fs-idp109253248">Humongous Bank is the only bank in the economy. The people in this economy have $20 million in money, and they deposit all their money in Humongous Bank.
  <list id="fs-idp59960320" list-type="enumerated" number-style="lower-alpha"><item>Humongous Bank decides on a policy of holding 100% reserves. Draw a T-account for the bank.</item>
  <item>Humongous Bank is required to hold 5% of its existing $20 million as reserves, and to loan out the rest. Draw a T-account for the bank after it has made its first round of loans.</item>
  <item>Assume that Humongous bank is part of a multibank system. How much will money supply increase with that original $19 million loan?</item>
  </list></para>
